{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":319,"text":"This is about a hidden corner of the labor market."},{"time":3902,"text":"It's the world of people who need to work ultra-flexibly,"},{"time":7535,"text":"if they're to work at all."},{"time":8852,"text":"So think, for instance,"},{"time":10019,"text":"of someone who has a recurring but unpredictable medical condition,"},{"time":13637,"text":"or somebody who's caring for a dependent adult,"},{"time":16420,"text":"or a parent with complex child care needs."},{"time":19267,"text":"Their availability for work can be such that it's,"},{"time":22425,"text":"\"A few hours today."},{"time":24118,"text":"Maybe I can work tomorrow, but I don't know if and when yet.\""},{"time":27718,"text":"And it's extraordinarily difficult for these people"},{"time":30237,"text":"to find the work that they so often need very badly."},{"time":33266,"text":"Which is a tragedy because there are employers"},{"time":36085,"text":"who can use pools of very flexible local people"},{"time":39391,"text":"booked completely ad hoc around when that person wants to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43290,"text":"Imagine that you run a cafe."},{"time":45891,"text":"It's mid-morning, the place is filling up."},{"time":47558,"text":"You're going to have a busy lunchtime rush."},{"time":49141,"text":"If you could get two extra workers for 90 minutes"},{"time":52458,"text":"to start in an hour's time,"},{"time":55112,"text":"you'd do it, but they'd have to be reliable, inducted in how your cafe works."},{"time":60070,"text":"They'd have to be available at very competitive rates."},{"time":61946,"text":"They'd have to be bookable in about the next minute."},{"time":65113,"text":"In reality, no recruitment agency wants to handle that sort of business,"},{"time":69045,"text":"so you are going to muddle by, understaffed."},{"time":72428,"text":"And it's not just caterers, it's hoteliers, it's retailers,"},{"time":74746,"text":"it's anyone who provides services to the public or businesses."},{"time":78045,"text":"There's all sorts of organizations that can use these pools of very flexible people,"},{"time":82578,"text":"possibly already once they've been inducted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85729,"text":"At this level of the labor market,"},{"time":87762,"text":"what you need is a marketplace for spare hours."},{"time":91612,"text":"They do exist. Here's how they work."},{"time":93729,"text":"So in this example, a distribution company has said,"},{"time":97196,"text":"we've got a rush order that we've got to get out of the warehouse tomorrow morning."},{"time":100479,"text":"Show us everyone who's available."},{"time":101879,"text":"It's found 31 workers."},{"time":103530,"text":"Everybody on this screen is genuinely available at those specific hours tomorrow."},{"time":107062,"text":"They're all contactable in time for this booking."},{"time":109396,"text":"They've all defined the terms on which they will accept bookings."},{"time":113397,"text":"And this booking is within all the parameters for each individual."},{"time":116811,"text":"And they would all be legally compliant by doing this booking."},{"time":119372,"text":"Of course, they're all trained to work in warehouses."},{"time":121296,"text":"You can select as many of them as you want."},{"time":123511,"text":"They're from multiple agencies."},{"time":124963,"text":"It's calculated the charge rate for each person for this specific booking."},{"time":128895,"text":"And it's monitoring their reliability."},{"time":131229,"text":"The people on the top row are the provenly reliable ones."},{"time":134229,"text":"They're likely to be more expensive."},{"time":135978,"text":"In an alternative view of this pool of local, very flexible people,"},{"time":139179,"text":"here's a market research company,"},{"time":140862,"text":"and it's inducted maybe 25 local people in how to do street interviewing."},{"time":144812,"text":"And they've got a new campaign. They want to run it next week."},{"time":147497,"text":"And they're looking at how many of the people they've inducted"},{"time":150896,"text":"are available each hour next week."},{"time":153178,"text":"And they'll then decide when to do their street interviews."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155912,"text":"But is there more that could be done"},{"time":158529,"text":"for this corner of the labor market?"},{"time":160279,"text":"Because right now there are so many people"},{"time":162965,"text":"who need whatever economic opportunity they can get."},{"time":166563,"text":"Let's make it personal."},{"time":168613,"text":"Imagine that a young woman -- base of the economic pyramid,"},{"time":171396,"text":"very little prospect of getting a job --"},{"time":173596,"text":"what economic activity could she theoretically engage in?"},{"time":177312,"text":"Well, she might be willing to work odd hours"},{"time":179596,"text":"in a call center, in a reception area, in a mail room."},{"time":182896,"text":"She may be interested in providing local services to her community:"},{"time":186228,"text":"babysitting, local deliveries, pet care."},{"time":188779,"text":"She may have possessions that she would like to trade"},{"time":191916,"text":"at times she doesn't need them."},{"time":193162,"text":"So she might have a sofa bed in her front room that she would like to let out."},{"time":196761,"text":"She might have a bike, a video games console she only uses occasionally."},{"time":200929,"text":"And you're probably thinking -- because you're all very web-aware --"},{"time":204330,"text":"yes, and we're in the era of collaborative consumption,"},{"time":206895,"text":"so she can go online and do all this."},{"time":208655,"text":"She can go to Airbnb to list her sofa bed,"},{"time":211313,"text":"she can go to TaskRabbit.com and say, \"I want to do local deliveries,\" and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215197,"text":"These are good sites, but I believe we can go a step further."},{"time":220547,"text":"And the key to that is a philosophy that we call modern markets for all."},{"time":227161,"text":"Markets have changed beyond recognition in the last 20 years,"},{"time":231712,"text":"but only for organizations at the top of the economy."},{"time":235396,"text":"If you're a Wall Street trader, you now take it for granted"},{"time":238396,"text":"that you sell your financial assets in a system of markets"},{"time":241312,"text":"that identifies the most profitable opportunities for you in real time,"},{"time":244895,"text":"executes on that in microseconds within the boundaries you've set."},{"time":248548,"text":"It analyzes supply and demand and pricing"},{"time":251980,"text":"and tells you where your next wave of opportunities are coming from."},{"time":254073,"text":"It manages counterparty risk in incredibly sophisticated ways."},{"time":257623,"text":"It's all extremely low overhead."},{"time":260057,"text":"What have we gained at the bottom of the economy"},{"time":263058,"text":"in terms of markets in the last 20 years?"},{"time":267152,"text":"Basically classified adverts with a search facility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273311,"text":"So why do we have this disparity"},{"time":275324,"text":"between these incredibly sophisticated markets at the top of the economy"},{"time":278874,"text":"that are increasingly sucking more and more activity and resource"},{"time":282490,"text":"out of the main economy into this rarefied level of trading,"},{"time":285939,"text":"and what the rest of us have?"},{"time":288323,"text":"A modern market is more than a website;"},{"time":291389,"text":"it's a web of interoperable marketplaces,"},{"time":294008,"text":"back office mechanisms, regulatory regimes,"},{"time":296542,"text":"settlement mechanisms, liquidity sources and so on."},{"time":301439,"text":"And when a Wall Street trader comes into work in the morning,"},{"time":304590,"text":"she does not write a listing for every financial derivative she wants to sell today"},{"time":309789,"text":"and then post that listing on multiple websites"},{"time":312405,"text":"and wait for potential buyers to get in touch"},{"time":314905,"text":"and start negotiating the terms on which she might trade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318622,"text":"In the early days of this modern markets technology,"},{"time":321521,"text":"the financial institutions worked out"},{"time":323589,"text":"how they could leverage their buying power, their back office processes,"},{"time":327221,"text":"their relationships, their networks"},{"time":329521,"text":"to shape these new markets that would create all this new activity."},{"time":334111,"text":"They asked governments for supporting regulatory regimes,"},{"time":337200,"text":"and in a lot of cases they got it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339834,"text":"But throughout the economy,"},{"time":341784,"text":"there are facilities that could likewise leverage"},{"time":344602,"text":"a new generation of markets"},{"time":346201,"text":"for the benefit of all of us."},{"time":348934,"text":"And those facilities --"},{"time":350902,"text":"I'm talking about things like the mechanisms that prove our identity,"},{"time":354618,"text":"the licensing authorities"},{"time":356901,"text":"that know what each of us is allowed to do legally at any given time,"},{"time":360734,"text":"the processes by which we resolve disputes through official channels."},{"time":364402,"text":"These mechanisms, these facilities"},{"time":367251,"text":"are not in the gift of Craigslist or Gumtree or Yahoo,"},{"time":370800,"text":"they're controlled by the state."},{"time":373902,"text":"And the policymakers who sit on top of them"},{"time":376633,"text":"are, I suggest, simply not thinking about how those facilities could be used"},{"time":382851,"text":"to underpin a whole new era of markets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385634,"text":"Like everyone else, those policymakers are taking it for granted"},{"time":390351,"text":"that modern markets are the preserve"},{"time":392619,"text":"of organizations powerful enough to create them for themselves."},{"time":400530,"text":"Suppose we stopped taking that for granted."},{"time":403957,"text":"Suppose tomorrow morning the prime minister of Britain or the president of the U.S.,"},{"time":407123,"text":"or the leader of any other developed nation,"},{"time":409305,"text":"woke up and said, \"I'm never going to be able to create"},{"time":413156,"text":"all the jobs I need in the current climate."},{"time":415322,"text":"I have got to focus on whatever economic opportunity I can get to my citizens."},{"time":420656,"text":"And for that they have to be able to access state-of-the-art markets."},{"time":424623,"text":"How do I make that happen?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426991,"text":"And I think I can see a few eyes rolling."},{"time":429740,"text":"Politicians in a big, complex, sophisticated I.T. project?"},{"time":433522,"text":"Oh, that's going to be a disaster waiting to happen."},{"time":437052,"text":"Not necessarily."},{"time":440057,"text":"There is a precedent for technology-enabled service"},{"time":442905,"text":"that has been initiated by politicians in multiple countries"},{"time":446607,"text":"and has been hugely successful:"},{"time":449423,"text":"national lotteries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451873,"text":"Let's take Britain as an example."},{"time":453623,"text":"Our government didn't design the national lottery,"},{"time":456223,"text":"it didn't fund the national lottery, it doesn't operate the national lottery."},{"time":459006,"text":"It simply passed the National Lottery Act and this is what followed."},{"time":464157,"text":"This act defines what a national lottery will look like."},{"time":467422,"text":"It specifies certain benefits"},{"time":469090,"text":"that the state can uniquely bestow on the operators."},{"time":471773,"text":"And it puts some obligations on those operators."},{"time":474472,"text":"In terms of spreading gambling activity to the masses,"},{"time":477822,"text":"this was an unqualified success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480856,"text":"But let's suppose that our aim"},{"time":482640,"text":"is to bring new economic activity to the base of the pyramid."},{"time":486523,"text":"Could we use the same model?"},{"time":488673,"text":"I believe we could."},{"time":490457,"text":"So imagine that policymakers outlined a facility."},{"time":494573,"text":"Let's call it national e-markets, NEMs for short."},{"time":498557,"text":"Think of it as a regulated public utility."},{"time":500406,"text":"So it's on a par with the water supply or the road network."},{"time":503290,"text":"And it's a series of markets for low-level trade"},{"time":507406,"text":"that can be fulfilled by a person or a small company."},{"time":510223,"text":"And government has certain benefits"},{"time":512972,"text":"it can uniquely bestow on these markets."},{"time":515522,"text":"It's about public spending going through these markets"},{"time":518306,"text":"to buy public services at the local level."},{"time":520905,"text":"It's about interfacing these markets"},{"time":522640,"text":"direct into the highest official channels in the land."},{"time":526290,"text":"It's about enshrining government's role as a publicist for these markets."},{"time":529690,"text":"It's about deregulating some sectors"},{"time":532472,"text":"so that local people can enter them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533905,"text":"So, taxi journeys might be one example."},{"time":536157,"text":"And there are certain obligations that should go with those benefits"},{"time":540939,"text":"to be placed on the operators,"},{"time":542540,"text":"and the key one is, of course,"},{"time":544040,"text":"that the operators pay for everything,"},{"time":546906,"text":"including all the interfacing into the public sector."},{"time":549907,"text":"So imagine that the operators make their return"},{"time":553473,"text":"by building a percentage markup into each transaction."},{"time":556656,"text":"Imagine that there's a concession period"},{"time":559090,"text":"defined of maybe 15 years"},{"time":561523,"text":"in which they can take all these benefits and run with them."},{"time":565989,"text":"And imagine that the consortia who bid to run it are told,"},{"time":569306,"text":"whoever comes in at the lowest percentage markup on each transaction"},{"time":572939,"text":"to fund the whole thing"},{"time":574431,"text":"will get the deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575806,"text":"So government then exits the frame."},{"time":577606,"text":"This is now in the hands of the consortium."},{"time":579239,"text":"Either they are going to unlock an awful lot of economic opportunity"},{"time":581790,"text":"and make a percentage on all of it"},{"time":583874,"text":"or it's all going to crash and burn,"},{"time":585473,"text":"which is tough on their shareholders."},{"time":587090,"text":"It doesn't bother the taxpayer necessarily."},{"time":589540,"text":"And there would be no constraints on alternative markets."},{"time":594190,"text":"So this would just be one more choice"},{"time":596623,"text":"among millions of Internet forums."},{"time":599439,"text":"But it could be very different,"},{"time":601989,"text":"because having access to those state-backed facilities"},{"time":605607,"text":"could incentivize this consortium"},{"time":607940,"text":"to seriously invest in the service."},{"time":610057,"text":"Because they would have to get a lot of these small transactions going"},{"time":613124,"text":"to start making their return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614855,"text":"So we're talking about sectors like home hair care,"},{"time":619746,"text":"the hire of toys, farm work,"},{"time":623703,"text":"hire of clothes even, meals delivered to your door,"},{"time":627322,"text":"services for tourists, home care."},{"time":629129,"text":"This would be a world of very small trades, but very well-informed,"},{"time":635912,"text":"because national e-markets will deliver data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639779,"text":"So this is a local person"},{"time":642412,"text":"potentially deciding whether to enter the babysitting market."},{"time":645412,"text":"And they might be aware that they would have to fund vetting and training"},{"time":648261,"text":"if they wanted to go into that market."},{"time":649661,"text":"They'd have to do assessment interviews with local parents"},{"time":652279,"text":"who wanted a pool of babysitters."},{"time":653779,"text":"Is it worth their while?"},{"time":655180,"text":"Should they be looking at other sectors?"},{"time":656880,"text":"Should they be moving to another part of the country"},{"time":658764,"text":"where there's a shortage of babysitters?"},{"time":661013,"text":"This kind of data can become routine."},{"time":663363,"text":"And this data can be used by investors."},{"time":665397,"text":"So if there's a problem with a shortage of babysitters in some parts of the country"},{"time":668563,"text":"and the problem is nobody can afford the vetting and training,"},{"time":671462,"text":"an investor can pay for it"},{"time":673046,"text":"and the system will tithe back the enhanced earnings of the individuals"},{"time":676730,"text":"for maybe the next two years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678379,"text":"This is a world of atomized capitalism."},{"time":681680,"text":"So it's small trades by small people,"},{"time":683712,"text":"but it's very informed, safe, convenient, low-overhead and immediate."},{"time":690579,"text":"Some rough research suggests this could unlock"},{"time":693504,"text":"around 100 million pounds' worth a day of new economic activity"},{"time":697705,"text":"in a country the size of the U.K."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699655,"text":"Does that sound improbable to you?"},{"time":702388,"text":"That's what a lot of people said about turbo trading"},{"time":706521,"text":"in financial exchanges 20 years ago."},{"time":709573,"text":"Do not underestimate the transformative power"},{"time":712673,"text":"of truly modern markets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715829,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717455,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}